      <article class="position editable" data-id="1283089" id="position_1283089">

        <div class="col-sm-4 timetable-left">
          <h4><a class="content-editable" data-field="employer_org_name" data-placeholder="Company Name" href="http://www.mysmartprice.com/" rel="nofollow" target="_blank">MySmartPrice.com</a></h4>
          <h5 class="timetable-date"
              data-placeholder="yyyy - yyyy"><span class="nowrap">Jun 2014</span> - <span class="nowrap">Present</span></h5>
        </div>
        <div class="col-sm-8 timetable-right">
          <img class="holder" src="images/circle.png" alt="">
          <div class="article-body">
            <h4 class="content-editable" data-field="title" data-placeholder="Job Title">Product Engineer</h4>
            <div class="mce-editable"
                 data-field="description"
                 data-placeholder="Job Description">
              <p>Working as a backend developer to build and work around a platform which lets you discover the best products across a wide variety of categories across myriads of e-commerce stores by using our price comparison engine.</p><ol><li>Worked on a PHP based HTML data parser(crawler) to scrape all the available e-commerce information either by hitting stores APIs or crawling them.</li><li>Implemented Apache SOLR for indexing, searching and recommending relevant content to the users' search queries.</li><li>Single handedly handling 'Deals &amp; Offers' section of the <a href="http://www.mysmartprice.com/" rel="nofollow" target="_blank">website</a>, which includes challenges like:</li><ul><li>Figuring out source of the deals based on what's trending, user behaviour, page views and automating the whole process from identifying a deal to making it live on the site.</li><li>Setting up a popularity logic according to which deals are to be displayed by considering factors like page views, purchased items, likes &amp; dislikes, decay rate etc.</li></ul><li>Made an engine to identify trending products based on increase in user interaction with a product or it's sudden price drop using AWS technology named Kinesis for processing real time data.</li><li>Predicted product recommendations on the basis of collaborative filtering using technologies like Apache Spark, Hadoop, Mahout, HBase.</li></ol>
            </div>          </div>
        </div>

</article>      <article class="position editable" data-id="1283143" id="position_1283143">

